    {
        "content": "<p>I tried to use the latest rust-next branch, and there was still an error when compiling out-of-tree modules</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">error</span>: <span class=\"nc\">target</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">file</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s\">\"./scripts/target.json\"</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">does</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">not</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">exist</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p><a href=\"/user_uploads/35136/MQK6CAXss0C8yl6LBfUgKpP1/image.png\">image.png</a></p>\n<div class=\"message_inline_image\"><a href=\"/user_uploads/35136/MQK6CAXss0C8yl6LBfUgKpP1/image.png\" title=\"image.png\"><img src=\"/user_uploads/35136/MQK6CAXss0C8yl6LBfUgKpP1/image.png\"></a></div><p>Makefile is </p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">default</span>:\n    <span class=\"cp\">$(</span><span class=\"n\">MAKE</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">C</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"cp\">$(</span><span class=\"n\">KDIR</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">M</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"cp\">$$PWD</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">modules_install</span>: <span class=\"nc\">default</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"cp\">$(</span><span class=\"n\">MAKE</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">C</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"cp\">$(</span><span class=\"n\">KDIR</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">M</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"cp\">$$PWD</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">modules_install</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>Source code is same as minimal sample.</p>",
